item.title: CVE-2019-3740|2024-09-17T01:40:53.233Z -- dell -- rsa%20bsafe%20crypto-j
item.description: RSA BSAFE Crypto-J versions prior to 6.2.5 are vulnerable to an Information Exposure Through Timing Discrepancy vulnerabilities during DSA key generation. A malicious remote attacker could potentially exploit those vulnerabilities to recover DSA keys.
